The article announces several nominations and appointments made by the President of the United States. The nominations include Jerome H. Powell as Chairman of the Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System, John C. Anderson as United States Attorney for the District of New Mexico, Robin S. Bernstein as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Dominican Republic, Joseph D. Brown as United States Attorney for the Eastern District of Texas, John H. Durham as United States Attorney for the District of Connecticut, Christopher Ashley Ford as Assistant Secretary of State (International Security and Non-Proliferation), Brandon J. Fremin as United States Attorney for the Middle District of Louisiana, Robert K. Hur as United States Attorney for the District of Maryland, Jeffrey Kessler as Assistant Secretary of Commerce, Ryan K. Patrick as United States Attorney for the Southern District of Texas, and McGregor William Scott as United States Attorney for the Eastern District of California.